<p>The average SEO agency charges <a href="https://backlinko.com/seo-pricing">$2,500 to $5,000 per month</a> in 2026. A DIY approach costs $0 in fees but demands 10 to 15 hours of your time every week. Done-for-you SEO services fall somewhere in between, starting under $150 per month.</p>
<p>Most business owners pick the wrong model. They either overspend on an agency that treats them like one of 40 clients, or they attempt DIY and abandon it after 3 months when results do not materialize.</p>
<p>The decision between done-for-you vs DIY vs agency SEO is not about which model is "best." It is about which model fits your budget, your time, and your growth stage right now.</p>
<p>We have published 3,500+ blog posts across 70+ industries with a 92% average SEO score. We have worked with businesses that tried all three models. This guide covers what we have seen work and what we have seen fail.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn:</p>
<ul>
<li>The real cost of each SEO model (not just the sticker price)</li>
<li>How much time each model demands from you personally</li>
<li>When DIY SEO is the smartest move for your business</li>
<li>When hiring an agency actually delivers ROI</li>
<li>Why done-for-you SEO is replacing agencies for small businesses</li>
<li>A decision framework to pick the right model today</li>
</ul>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Done-for-you vs DIY vs agency SEO comparison overview" src="/images/blog/dfy-vs-diy-vs-agency-seo-overview.webp" /></p>
<h2>What Each SEO Model Actually Means</h2>
<p>Before comparing costs and results, you need to understand what you are actually buying with each model. The labels sound similar. The reality is not.</p>
<h3>DIY SEO</h3>
<p>You do everything yourself. Keyword research, content writing, on-page optimization, technical fixes, link building, and performance tracking. You use free or paid tools like Google Search Console, Ahrefs, or Semrush. You learn as you go.</p>
<p>DIY does not mean "free." It means you pay with time instead of money.</p>
<h3>Agency SEO</h3>
<p>You hire a team of specialists. A typical agency assigns an account manager, content strategist, technical SEO specialist, and link builder to your account. They handle strategy, execution, and reporting. You review monthly reports and approve deliverables.</p>
<p>Agency contracts usually lock you in for 6 to 12 months with monthly retainers.</p>
<h3>Done-for-You SEO</h3>
<p>A service handles specific SEO tasks on autopilot. Unlike an agency, done-for-you services typically focus on one or two pillars (like content creation or local SEO) rather than a full-service engagement. You do not manage the process. Content gets published automatically.</p>
<p>The key difference: agencies sell strategy and expertise. Done-for-you services sell output and execution.</p>
<h2>The Real Cost of Each SEO Model</h2>
<p>Cost is the first thing business owners compare. But the sticker price tells only half the story. Here is the full breakdown.</p>
