<h3>The Hidden Cost of DIY</h3>
<p>Your time has a dollar value. If you earn $75 per hour and spend 12 hours per week on SEO, that is $3,600 per month in opportunity cost. Add $200 for tools. Your real DIY cost is $3,800 per month.</p>
<p>That is more than most done-for-you services and nearly matches a mid-tier agency.</p>
<h3>The Hidden Cost of Agencies</h3>
<p>Agencies charge for strategy meetings, reporting calls, and account management. <a href="https://firstpagesage.com/seo-blog/seo-agency-pricing-survey/">According to First Page Sage</a>, the average agency retainer is $2,917 per month. But the real cost includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>2 to 4 hours per week reviewing deliverables and joining calls</li>
<li>Contract cancellation fees (often 30 to 90 days notice)</li>
<li>Add-on charges for "extra" content or link building campaigns</li>
<li>Onboarding fees that range from $500 to $5,000</li>
</ul>
<p>A $3,000 per month agency retainer often costs $4,000 to $5,000 when you add your time and hidden fees.</p>
<h3>The Done-for-You Cost Advantage</h3>
<p>Done-for-you <a href="/best/done-for-you-seo-services-small-business/">SEO services for small businesses</a> strip out the overhead. No account managers. No strategy calls. No reporting decks. The service publishes content, and you check the results.</p>
