<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How much does DIY SEO actually cost per month?</strong></p>
<p>The tool cost alone runs $99 to $449 per month for platforms like Ahrefs or Semrush. Add 10 to 15 hours per week of your time. If you value your time at $50 to $100 per hour, the real cost is $2,100 to $6,400 per month. The only scenario where DIY is truly cheap is when your time has low opportunity cost.</p>
<p><strong>Can a $99 per month service really compete with a $3,000 per month agency?</strong></p>
<p>On content volume, yes. Stacc publishes 30 optimized articles per month at $99. Most agencies deliver 4 to 8 articles at $3,000. On custom strategy, technical audits, and link building, agencies still hold an advantage. The right question is which output matters most for your situation.</p>
<p><strong>How long before I see results from done-for-you SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Initial ranking movement happens within 60 to 90 days. Meaningful organic traffic growth typically occurs at the 3 to 6 month mark. The compounding effect accelerates after 6 months as <a href="/blog/build-topical-authority/">topical authority</a> builds across your content library.</p>
<p><strong>Is it worth paying for an SEO agency if my budget is under $1,500?</strong></p>
<p>No. At that price point, most agencies assign junior staff or use templated strategies. You get better results from a done-for-you content service ($99 to $199) combined with DIY technical SEO. Save the agency budget for when you can afford $3,000+ per month.</p>
<p><strong>What if I start with DIY and switch to done-for-you later?</strong></p>
<p>That is a common and smart path. Start by learning SEO fundamentals through DIY. Once you understand what good SEO looks like, you can evaluate done-for-you output with an informed eye. The content you published during DIY still contributes to your domain authority.</p>
<p><strong>Do agencies guarantee rankings?</strong></p>
<p>No reputable agency guarantees specific rankings. Google does not allow anyone to guarantee placement. Agencies that promise "page 1 in 30 days" are almost always using outdated tactics that risk penalties. Look for agencies that guarantee process (publishing cadence, reporting frequency, response time) rather than outcomes.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Rank everywhere. Do nothing.</strong> Blog SEO, Local SEO, and Social on autopilot.
<a href="/pricing/">Start for $1 →</a></p>
</blockquote>
<p>The right SEO model for your business depends on where you are today, not where you want to be in 3 years. Start with the model that matches your current budget and time. Upgrade as revenue grows. The only wrong choice is doing nothing while your competitors <a href="/blog/increase-organic-traffic/">build organic traffic</a> every month.</p>
